1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,770
Your mind is a thought factory.

2
00:00:03,039 --> 00:00:07,170
It's a busy factory producing countless thoughts in one day.

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:16,849
Production in your thought factory is under the charge of two foremen, one of whom we will call Mr. Triumph and the other Mr. Defeat.

4
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:21,490
Mr. Triumph is in charge of manufacturing positive thoughts.

5
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:28,370
He specializes in producing reasons why you can, why you're qualified, why you will.

6
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:34,130
The other foreman, Mr. Defeat, produces negative, deprecating thoughts.

7
00:00:34,559 --> 00:00:41,329
He is your expert in developing reasons why you can't, why you're weak, why you're inadequate.

8
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:46,210
His specialty is the why-you-will-fail chain of thoughts.

9
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:51,410
Both Mr. Triumph and Mr. Defeat are intensely obedient.

10
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:53,970
They snap to attention immediately.

11
00:00:54,320 --> 00:01:00,289
All you need do to signal either foreman is to give the slightest mental beck and call.

12
00:01:00,559 --> 00:01:05,490
If the signal is positive, Mr. Triumph will step forward and go to work.

13
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:10,130
Likewise, a negative signal brings Mr. Defeat forward.

14
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:14,849
To see how these two foremen work for you, try this example.

15
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:18,529
Tell yourself, Today is a lousy day.

16
00:01:18,799 --> 00:01:25,730
This signals Mr. Defeat into action, and he manufactures some facts to prove you are right.

17
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,569
He suggests to you that it's too hot or it's too cold.

18
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:31,569
Business will be bad today.

19
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,930
Sales will drop.

20
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:35,010
Other people will be on edge.

21
00:01:35,039 --> 00:01:36,289
You may get sick.

22
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,770
Your wife will be in a fussy mood.

23
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:41,809
Mr. Defeat is tremendously efficient.

24
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,849
In just a few moments he's got you sold.

25
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:46,370
It is a bad day.

26
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:49,730
Before you know it, it is a heck of a bad day.

27
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:56,529
But tell yourself, today is a fine day, and Mr. Triumph is signaled forward to act.

28
00:01:56,720 --> 00:02:02,529
He tells you, this is a wonderful day, the weather is refreshing, it's good to be alive,

29
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:07,890
today you can catch up on some of your work, and then it is a good day.

30
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:14,210
In like fashion, Mr. Defeat can show you why you can't sell Mr. Smith.

31
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,010
Mr. Triumph will show you that you can.

32
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:24,370
Mr. Defeat will convince you that you will fail, while Mr. Triumph will demonstrate why you will succeed.

33
00:02:24,799 --> 00:02:33,410
Mr. Defeat will prepare a brilliant case against Tom, while Mr. Triumph will show you more reasons why you like Tom.

34
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:39,329
Now, the more work you give either of these two foremen, the stronger he becomes.

35
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:46,529
If Mr. Defeat is given more work to do, he adds personnel and takes up more space in your mind.

36
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:55,329
Eventually, he will take over the entire thought-manufacturing division and virtually all thought will be of a negative nature.

37
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,569
The only wise thing to do is fire Mr. Defeat.

38
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,930
You don't need him.

39
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:05,250
You don't want him around telling you that you can't, you're not up to it,

40
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:06,770
you'll fail, and so on.

41
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:11,809
Mr. Defeat won't help you get where you want to go, so boot him out.

42
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:15,569
Use Mr. Triumph 100% of the time.

43
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:20,609
When any thought enters your mind, ask Mr. Triumph to go to work for you.

44
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:23,170
He'll show you how you can succeed.

